[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:40[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Remote Code Execution [1m([0mRCE[1m)[0m vulnerability has been detected in Apache Tika's RTF  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parser through fuzzing. The vulnerability stems from unrestricted deserialization   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         of externally controlled data, where arbitrary Java objects can be instantiated     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         based on untrusted input. This occurs during the parsing of RTF documents           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         containing embedded objects, allowing potential attackers to execute arbitrary code [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         if malicious classes are available on the classpath.                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Vulnerability Type                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This is a Java deserialization vulnerability classified as a **Remote Code          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Execution [1m([0mRCE[1m)[0m** security issue. The fuzzer specifically identifies it as allowing [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"Unrestricted class/object creation based on externally controlled data,"[0m which is  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         a critical security flaw that can enable attackers to execute arbitrary code on the [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         target system.                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Issue Details                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The vulnerability is triggered during the processing of RTF documents by Apache     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika. The stack trace reveals the following execution flow:                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. The RTF parser [1m([0m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser`[1m)[0m begins parsing [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         an RTF document                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. During text extraction [1m([0m`TextExtractor.extract`[1m)[0m, the parser processes RTF group [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         structures                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. When encountering the end of a group [1m([0m`processGroupEnd`[1m)[0m, the `RTFEmbObjHandler` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         handles embedded objects                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. In `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject` at line [1;36m217[0m, the code performs Java  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         object deserialization using `[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. The deserialization process invokes a custom `readObject` method [1m([0mat             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `jaz.Zer.readObject` line [1;36m377[0m[1m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m. This triggers the security check that detects and reports the unrestricted       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization vulnerability                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The security detection mechanism [1m([0m`jaz.Zer.reportFinding`[1m)[0m identifies this as a     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         high-severity issue because the deserialization occurs on data that originates from [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         external, untrusted sources [1m([0mthe RTF file content[1m)[0m.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Key Observations                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - **Entry Point**: The vulnerability is reached through                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mRTFParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`, which serves as the fuzzing harness entry point       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - **Critical Code Path**: The problematic deserialization occurs in                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject` at    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         line [1;36m217[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - **Attack Vector**: Maliciously crafted RTF documents containing embedded objects  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         can trigger arbitrary object instantiation                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - **Severity**: Classified as `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh`, indicating critical        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         security impact                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - **Deduplication Token**: aa5f725795b842b8 [1m([0mfor tracking this specific issue       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instance[1m)[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Areas for Investigation                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         To obtain a comprehensive understanding of this vulnerability, the following        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         codebase components should be investigated:                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **RTFEmbObjHandler class**                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler`[1m)[0m:                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Examine the `handleCompletedObject` method, particularly line [1;36m217[0m where        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization occurs                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Understand how embedded objects are extracted from RTF content                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review object validation and sanitization mechanisms [1m([0mif any[1m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **TextExtractor class** [1m([0m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor`[1m)[0m:  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Analyze the `processGroupEnd` method [1m([0mline [1;36m1475[0m[1m)[0m that triggers embedded object [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         handling                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review the overall RTF parsing flow in the `extract` method                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Identify where external RTF data is processed and passed to object handlers    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **RTFParser class** [1m([0m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser`[1m)[0m:          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Examine the parsing initialization and configuration                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review the `parseInline` and `parse` methods to understand the overall parsing [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         architecture                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Embedded Object Handling**:                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Investigate how RTF embedded objects are represented internally                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Determine if there are any whitelisting or blacklisting mechanisms for         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserializable classes                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review the complete lifecycle of embedded object processing from parsing to    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **Security Controls**:                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Check if there are existing deserialization filters or safeguards in the       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         codebase                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review configuration options that might control deserialization behavior       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Examine any existing security documentation or guidelines related to RTF       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parsing                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:        byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m embObjBytes = [0m[1;35mreadBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mis, dataSz[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mclassName.toLowerCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLocale.ROOT[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"package"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:            return [0m[1;35mhandlePackage[0m[1;39m([0m[39membObjBytes, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mclassName.toLowerCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLocale.ROOT[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"pbrush"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m119[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95msimple[0m[39m bitmap bytes[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m120[0m[39m:            return embObjBytes;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m121[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m122[0m[39m:            UnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream embIs = [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.setByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39membObjBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:            boolean hasPoifs;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m124[0m[39m:            try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:                hasPoifs = [0m[1;35mhasPOIFSHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[39membIs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordEmbeddedStreamException[0m[1;39m([0m[39me, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:                return embObjBytes;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhasPoifs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m131[0m[39m:                try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m132[0m[39m:                    return [0m[1;35mhandleEmbeddedPOIFS[0m[1;39m([0m[39membIs, metadata, [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munknownFilenameCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m133[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m134[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordEmbeddedStreamException[0m[1;39m([0m[39me, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m137[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m138[0m[39m:        return embObjBytes;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m139[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Analysis[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified a **Remote[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode Execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRCE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability** in Apache Tika's RTF parser stemming from [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munrestricted Java deserialization. The vulnerability is in [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m[1;36m215[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m217[0m[39m, where arbitrary Java [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects from untrusted RTF files are deserialized without any validation or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiltering.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in the `JAVA_OBJDATA` code path:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When the RTF parser encounters `\javaobjdata` control word, it collects [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhex-encoded bytes[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- These bytes are directly deserialized using `new [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No `ObjectInputFilter`, class whitelisting, or validation is performed[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This allows arbitrary object instantiation based on attacker-controlled data[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Intentional Feature**: The `javaobjdata` feature was deliberately implemented [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith its own state [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but without security considerations[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Contrast with Safe Implementation**: The `objdata` path uses [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFObjDataParser` which safely parses structured OLE/Package formats without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Active Test**: `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test demonstrates the feature works but uses [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly benign `String` objects[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No Security Controls**: No `ObjectInputFilter`, no class restrictions, no [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity warnings in documentation[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Attack Vector[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```rtf[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m[39m\*\javaobjdata <hex_encoded_malicious_serialized_object>[0m[1;39m}[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attacker can embed a malicious serialized Java object in an RTF file. When Tika [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparses it, the deserialization process can trigger gadget chains if vulnerable [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses exist on the classpath, leading to RCE.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Complete Removal of Unsafe Deserialization Feature[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe safest and most appropriate fix is to **completely remove the `javaobjdata` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization feature**. This is justified because:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **No legitimate use case**: There's no evidence this feature is used in standard[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTF documents[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Inherent security risk**: Java deserialization from untrusted input is a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell-known critical vulnerability class[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Alternative exists**: The safe `objdata` path handles embedded objects [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperly using structured parsing[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Steps[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Remove JAVA_OBJDATA State Handling in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File**: [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micro[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/RTFEmbObjHandler.jav[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma`[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Remove the ObjectInputStream import** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m21[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove: `import java.io.ObjectInputStream;`[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Remove `[0m[1;35mstartJavaObjData[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m102[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m105[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete the entire method[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Remove JAVA_OBJDATA from enum** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m283[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the `EMB_STATE` enum, remove `JAVA_OBJDATA`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep only: `PICT, OBJDATA, NADA`[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Remove JAVA_OBJDATA case in `[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete the entire `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstate == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The method should only handle `OBJDATA`, `PICT`, and `NADA` states[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Remove javaobjdata Control Word Handling in `TextExtractor.java`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File**: [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micro[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/TextExtractor.java`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Remove javaobjdata control word handler** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1274[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1276[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete the entire `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mequals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"javaobjdata"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents the parser from entering the vulnerable state[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Remove javaobjdata from parsing condition** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m487[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change: `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgroupState.objdata == true || groupState.javaobjdata == [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrue || groupState.pictDepth == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - To: `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgroupState.objdata == true || groupState.pictDepth == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Remove javaobjdata state handling in `[0m[1;35mprocessGroupEnd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1473[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1479[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete the entire `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgroupState.javaobjdata == true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Remove javaobjdata State from `GroupState.java`[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File**: [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micro[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/GroupState.java`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Remove javaobjdata field** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m38[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m39[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete: `[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95min[0m[39m javaobjdata`[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete: `public boolean javaobjdata;`[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Remove javaobjdata from state inheritance** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m67[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete: `javaobjdata = other.javaobjdata;`[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Remove Test for javaobjdata Feature[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File**: [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Remove or modify `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m516[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m528[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete the entire test method[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete helper methods: `[0m[1;35mwriteObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mwrap[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mserialize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m530[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m558[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These are only used for testing the vulnerable feature[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Remove ObjectOutputStream import** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m27[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove: `import java.io.ObjectOutputStream;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif not used elsewhere[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: Remove Test RTF File[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File**: [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micro[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msoft-module/src/test/resources/test-documents/rtf/rtfJavaObjTemplate.rtf`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This test file is only used for the `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test and can be removed[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Justification[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Security First**: Removing unsafe deserialization eliminates the entire attack[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msurface[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **No Functionality Loss**: There's no evidence of legitimate use of [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`javaobjdata` in real-world RTF documents[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: The safe `objdata` and `pict` handling remain [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompletely intact[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Follows Best Practices**: Aligns with OWASP guidelines to avoid [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization of untrusted data[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Consistent with Codebase**: Other embedded object types use safe structured [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee `RTFObjDataParser`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Alternative Approach [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIf Feature Must Be Retained[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIf there's a business requirement to keep the feature, implement strict [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization filtering:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Add ObjectInputFilter** with strict class allowlist:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ObjectInputStream ois = new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mois.setObjectInputFilter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfilterInfo -> [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       Class<?> clazz = [0m[1;35mfilterInfo.serialClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mclazz == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return ObjectInputFilter.Status.UNDECIDED;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Allowlist only safe classes[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mclazz == String.class || [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           clazz == Integer.class ||[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           clazz == Long.class ||[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m other safe primitives/wrappers[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mclazz.isPrimitive[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return ObjectInputFilter.Status.ALLOWED;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return ObjectInputFilter.Status.REJECTED;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Add configuration option** to disable the feature by default[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Add security warnings** in documentation[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, **removal is strongly recommended** as the safest approach.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Impact Analysis[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Breaking Changes**:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test will be removed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpected[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any code using `\javaobjdata` RTF control word will no longer deserialize objects[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The feature was never part of RTF standard, so real-world impact should be [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mminimal[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Preserved Functionality**:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All other RTF parsing remains intact[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Safe `objdata` handling via `RTFObjDataParser` continues to work[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Picture/bitmap extraction continues to work[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing non-javaobjdata tests pass[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Test Suite Impact**: One test will be removed, but this is expected for [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity fixes[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Backward Compatibility**: RTF files with `\javaobjdata` will have that content[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mignored [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTF's `\*` prefix means [0m[32m"skip if not understood"[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No Performance Impact**: Removing code paths improves performance slightly[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### References from Codebase[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Safe pattern**: `RTFObjDataParser` demonstrates safe embedded object handling [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musing structured parsing[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Security awareness**: `TikaServerConfig` shows the project has security [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocumentation for other features [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCVE-[0m[1;36m2015[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m3271[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Custom ClassLoader**: `ForkObjectInputStream` shows awareness of [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization concerns, though not used in RTF parser[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor.processGroupEnd[0m[1m([0mTextExtractor.ja [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         v[1;92ma:1475[0m[1m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor.extract[0m[1m([0mTextExtractor.jav[1;92ma:482[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor.extract[0m[1m([0mTextExtractor.jav[1;92ma:466[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser.parseInline[0m[1m([0mRTFParser.jav[1;92ma:96[0m[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser.parse[0m[1m([0mRTFParser.jav[1;92ma:70[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1m([0mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:53[0m[1m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:40[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a Remote Code Execution vulnerability detected by a fuzzer     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mJazzer[1m)[0m in Apache Tika's RTF parser. The vulnerability arises from unrestricted    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization of Java objects embedded in RTF documents, which can lead to        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         arbitrary code execution. The patch attempt aimed to remove the deserialization     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         functionality entirely by eliminating support for Java object data [1m([0m`javaobjdata`[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in RTF parsing. However, the patch resulted in a compilation failure because it     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         removed the `JAVA_OBJDATA` enum value from the `EMB_STATE` enum but left a          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         reference to it in the code at line [1;36m102[0m of `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Initial Issue Analysis                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer identified a critical security vulnerability with the following          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         characteristics:                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Exception Type**: `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indicating a high-severity Remote Code Execution vulnerability                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Root Cause Location**: The stack trace shows the vulnerability is triggered in [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` at line [1;36m217[0m, which calls                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Attack Vector**: The vulnerability allows unrestricted class/object creation   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         based on externally controlled data from RTF files                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Call Chain**: The issue occurs when:                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mRTFParser.parse[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` processes an RTF document                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mTextExtractor.extract[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` processes group elements                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mTextExtractor.processGroupEnd[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` completes object processing                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` deserializes embedded Java objects  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         using `[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The critical code path involves deserialization of untrusted data from RTF files,   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which is a well-known attack vector for Remote Code Execution vulnerabilities in    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Java applications.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Patch Attempt Description                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch attempted to completely remove the Java object deserialization            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         functionality across three files:                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **RTFEmbObjHandler.java**:                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed the import for `java.io.ObjectInputStream`                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Deleted the entire code block handling `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` [1m([0mlines         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m-[1;36m223[0m[1m)[0m, which included:                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - Creating an `ObjectInputStream` from byte array                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - Calling `[1;35mreadObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to deserialize the object                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - Setting metadata about the embedded class                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - Converting the object to string for extraction                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed the `JAVA_OBJDATA` value from the `EMB_STATE` enum                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **GroupState.java**:                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed the `javaobjdata` boolean field from the class                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed the line copying the `javaobjdata` state in the copy constructor       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **TextExtractor.java**:                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Modified the condition at line [1;36m487[0m to remove the check for                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `groupState.javaobjdata`                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed the control destination handler for [32m"javaobjdata"[0m [1m([0mlines [1;36m1273[0m-[1;36m1275[0m[1m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that set the flag and started Java object data processing                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed the entire code block handling `groupState.javaobjdata == true` in     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mprocessGroupEnd[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` [1m([0mlines [1;36m1473[0m-[1;36m1480[0m[1m)[0m which called                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35membObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Compilation Error                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch resulted in a compilation error:                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m[[0mERROR[1m][0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/project-parent/tika/tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-m[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35modules/tika-parser-microsoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35mrtf/[0m[95mRTFEmbObjHandler.java[0m:[1m[[0m[1;36m102[0m,[1;36m26[0m[1m][0m cannot find symbol                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           symbol:   variable JAVA_OBJDATA                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           location: class org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.EMB_STATE   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This indicates that while the patch removed the `JAVA_OBJDATA` enum value from the  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `EMB_STATE` enum definition, there is still a reference to `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         at line [1;36m102[0m in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` that was not removed by the patch.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Areas for Further Investigation                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         To fully understand and resolve this issue, the following areas should be           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         investigated:                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **RTFEmbObjHandler.java line [1;36m102[0m**: The exact code at this line needs to be      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         examined to understand what reference to `JAVA_OBJDATA` exists there. This is       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         likely in a method that was not shown in the patch context, such as:                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The `[1;35mstartJavaObjData[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method that was referenced but not shown in the patch [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A switch statement or conditional that checks the state                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - State initialization or transition logic                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Complete state management**: All locations where `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` is   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         referenced should be identified, including:                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - State transitions in `RTFEmbObjHandler`                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Any initialization code                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Any logging or debugging statements                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Related methods in RTFEmbObjHandler**: Methods that were referenced but not    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         modified in the patch:                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mstartJavaObjData[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method [1m([0mcalled in TextExtractor.java[1m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Any other methods that might interact with the Java object data state          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Test coverage**: Existing unit tests or integration tests that may reference   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Java object data functionality and would need to be updated or removed              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **Documentation and specifications**: Any documentation about RTF format support [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that mentions Java object embedding, to understand if this feature is part of the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         RTF specification or a Tika-specific extension                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The incomplete removal of references to the `JAVA_OBJDATA` state is the immediate   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         cause of the compilation failure and must be addressed to successfully apply the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         security fix.                                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m555[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
